prompt: Close-up macro shot of a fragment of ancient Native American pottery, showcasing the texture and composition of the clay. Focus on the inclusions (sand, mica, crushed shell) within the clay matrix. The lighting should be soft and diffused, highlighting the imperfections and age of the pottery. Depth of field should be shallow, blurring the background to emphasize the pottery fragment. Style: Photorealistic, archaeological documentation. --ar 16:9
name: how-to-identify-old-indian-pottery-image-1.png

prompt: A weathered hand holding a partially reconstructed Native American pottery vessel against a backdrop of a Southwestern desert landscape at sunset. The pottery is decorated with geometric patterns typical of the Anasazi culture. The light should be warm and golden, casting long shadows. The composition should emphasize the contrast between the fragility of the pottery and the vastness of the desert. Style: Photorealistic, evocative, National Geographic. --ar 16:9
name: how-to-identify-old-indian-pottery-image-2.png

prompt: Overhead studio shot of several pottery shards laid out on a light-colored canvas. Each shard displays different techniques (coiling, paddling, incising) and decorative motifs from various Native American tribes. Include a measuring tape and magnifying glass as tools of analysis. The lighting is even and bright, ensuring clarity and detail. The composition is clean and organized, emphasizing the diversity of pottery styles. Style: Photorealistic, educational, scientific documentation. --ar 16:9
name: how-to-identify-old-indian-pottery-image-3.png

prompt: A Native American elder sitting outdoors, demonstrating the traditional hand-coiling method of pottery creation. The elder is working on a new pot, using locally sourced clay. The background shows a traditional adobe home and pottery drying in the sun. The light is natural and warm, capturing the wisdom and artistry of the craftsperson. Style: Photorealistic, documentary, respectful and culturally sensitive. --ar 16:9
name: how-to-identify-old-indian-pottery-image-4.png

prompt: A side-by-side comparison of a genuine ancient Native American pottery fragment and a modern reproduction. The ancient fragment shows signs of weathering and use, while the reproduction is pristine and brightly colored. The background is a neutral gray, allowing for easy comparison. The lighting is even and balanced, highlighting the differences in texture, color, and construction. Style: Photorealistic, informative, forensic analysis. --ar 16:9
name: how-to-identify-old-indian-pottery-image-5.png
